EXT. MOUNTAIN VIEW CEMETERY - AFTERNOON

The rain has stopped.

The cemetery has not changed.

No choir.

No umbrellas.

No one pretending this is sacred.

A maintenance cart waits outside the columbarium.

The four men approach.

This time, Solomon is paperwork.

INT. COLUMBARIUM - MOMENTS LATER

A CEMETERY ADMINISTRATOR checks Malik's identification against the release.

She is kind in the practiced way of someone whose office never receives good news.

ADMINISTRATOR
This normally takes one business day.

MALIK
We were told the order was already
