Removes a driver.

The same corridor.

The same sealed square.

Kai studies the bolts.

Three in a row.

The groundskeeper fits the driver to the first bolt.

METAL WHINES against stone.

Kai's shoulders tighten.

The second bolt.

The third.

The panel releases with a soft vacuum of trapped air.

The niche opens.

Dark.

Ordinary.

The brass urn waits exactly where they left it.

The groundskeeper reaches inside.

Bode stops him.

BODE
Please.

The groundskeeper steps back.

Malik moves forward.

Places both hands around the urn.

The brass is colder than the room.

He lifts.

