We buried something.

Leave the name.

Ade understands.

The groundskeeper replaces the empty panel.

One bolt.

Then another.

Sealing nothing.

Kai raises his camera.

Frames the empty niche before it disappears.

Through the viewfinder—

Only stone.

He takes the photograph.

CLICK.

The panel closes.

The final bolt tightens.

Malik carries the urn toward the exit.

Ade offers his hands.

No joke.

Malik gives him the urn.

Immediately.

The administrator notices the exchange.

She looks away to grant it privacy.

EXT. MOUNTAIN VIEW CEMETERY - CONTINUOUS

Ade steps into pale afternoon light carrying Solomon.

Kai beside him.

Malik behind.

Bode last.

At the car, Ade stops.

