INT. SOLOMON'S HOUSE - VARIOUS - NIGHT

The house becomes a departure board.

In the dining room—

Malik builds four travel folders.

Flights.

Vaccinations.

Cemetery release.

Emergency numbers.

Every document duplicated.

Then duplicated again.

He writes:

DAY 1.

DAY 2.

DAY 3.

Stops at:

DAY 9.

Across the page, the ink from his torn signature has bled into a small black branch.

He closes the folder over it.

In Solomon's bedroom—

Ade lays clothes across the bed.

Too many shirts.

Not enough underwear.

Three pairs of shoes.

He removes one pair.

Adds it back.

On the chair:

Solomon's cardigan.

Ade touches the sleeve.

Raises it to his face.

The smell is already leaving.

He folds the cardigan.

Places it in his suitcase.

Then takes it out.

Leaves it on Solomon's pillow.

